article.description: Coll. of Charleston 88, S. Carolina St. 73
article.headline: Coll. of Charleston 88, S. Carolina St. 73
article.linkText: Coll. of Charleston 88, S. Carolina St. 73
article.story: CHARLESTON, S.C. -- Andrew Goudelock scored 22 points and Casaan Breeden added 20 to help the College of Charleston defeat South Carolina State 88-73 on Saturday. Breeden was 8 of 10 from the field as the Cougars (7-6) shot 52.2 percent in the game (36 of 69). College of Charleston jumped out to 14-2 lead on Donavan Monroe's layup with 15:34 left in the first half and wasn't threatened the rest of the way. The Cougars outrebounded South Carolina State 40-31 with Jeremy Simmons grabbing nine. Tyvon Williams led four players in double figures, scoring 17 points for the Bulldogs (6-5), who lost their third straight. Jason Flagler and Arsenio Williams added 12 apiece for South Carolina State and Darnell Porter chipped in 11. The Bulldogs were 4 of 18 from 3-point range (22.2 percent).
